{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b33207b2-b70a-4b81-8ef7-afc16f077705","content":"\n\n","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_yCaRXhJedqunr6xY93AsZY","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Reviewing project context"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_SpOBvKUCpmZizAUI7OA1zz","name":"view","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-778235a578af4ac5885ef7f65eb857fb/TestProject.csproj"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"view the file at /tmp/sv-778235a578af4ac5885ef7f65eb857fb/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"003baaa4-2605-4575-9fe3-e705b6afde0d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change between MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 and 4.1.0 regarding test discovery with vstest.console. This is a knowledge question about MSTest SDK changes, not a code investigation task.\n\nLet me look at the files in the working directory to understand the context better, but this is primarily a knowledge-based question.\n\nI know that MSTest.Sdk 3.x included both the VSTest runner and the newer Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner. Starting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0, the VSTest runner support was removed by default — the SDK only ships with Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This means `vstest.console` can no longer discover or run tests because the VSTest adapter/test host isn't included.\n\n\nI should check the project file to see what version they're using and provide specific guidance on how to restore VSTest compatibility if needed.","outputTokens":318},"id":"7b18489f-1ca9-4ba4-aa10-8dbaec0ac135","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:06:14.938Z","parentId":"ff2ab0e2-ab0e-4df0-9040-823386ca42b5"}
