{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4a8d10a1-45cd-4715-9323-523c769b6c9d","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest runner by default.**\n\nIn 3.x, the SDK shipped *both* the legacy VSTest adapter and the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner. Starting with **4.0**, only Microsoft.Testing.Platform is included — `vstest.console` no longer has an adapter to discover your tests.\n\nYou have two options:\n\n### Option 1 — Switch your CI to `dotnet test` (recommended)\n`dotnet test` works with Microsoft.Testing.Platform out of the box. Replace `vstest.console` calls with:\n```\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj\n```\n\n### Option 2 — Re-enable the VSTest adapter\nIf you must keep `vstest.console`, add this to your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>false</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\nOr explicitly add the VSTest adapter package:\n```xml\n<ItemGroup>\n  <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest.TestAdapter\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\n**Option 1 is the recommended path forward** — Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the successor to VSTest and offers better performance and parallelism.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"003baaa4-2605-4575-9fe3-e705b6afde0d","outputTokens":334},"id":"d98109ab-66ec-428c-88cd-e531830a0409","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:06:22.511Z","parentId":"9864f25e-9e13-4b6e-a1a2-bfb920121f2f"}
